tidewatch (3.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian package release for Milestone 3
  * Renamed project from thugshells/belabox-metrics to tidewatch
  * Add systemd watchdog integration with Type=notify
  * Add process locking to prevent double-start
  * Implement automatic database migrations on upgrade
  * Add comprehensive systemd security hardening
  * Support for arm64 and armhf architectures
  * GPG-signed packages with checksums
  * Automated GitHub Actions build pipeline

 -- Tani Aura <111664369+taniwha3@users.noreply.github.com>  Sun, 13 Oct 2024 23:00:00 -0700

tidewatch (2.0.0-1) stable; urgency=low

  * Milestone 2 release
  * Add database deduplication and checkpoint tracking
  * Add configuration file support (YAML)
  * Implement health check endpoints
  * Add systemd watchdog and process locking packages
  * Add retry logic with exponential backoff
  * Add clock skew detection
  * macOS support improvements

 -- Tani Aura <111664369+taniwha3@users.noreply.github.com>  Sun, 06 Oct 2024 12:00:00 -0700

tidewatch (1.0.0-1) stable; urgency=low

  * Milestone 1 release (as belabox-metrics)
  * Initial metrics collection implementation
  * Support for CPU, memory, disk, network, and thermal metrics
  * SQLite storage with local buffering
  * VictoriaMetrics export support

 -- Tani Aura <111664369+taniwha3@users.noreply.github.com>  Sun, 29 Sep 2024 12:00:00 -0700
